The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Tokyo, July 7: Toyota Motor, and its subsidiary, Daihatsu Motor, will build a new plant in India to produce small cars from 2007, the Nihon Keizai Shimbun has reported. The plant will come up in Bangalore and produce 100,000 cars annually at the initial stage. The investment is likely to be around 12 billion yen (more than $100 million), the paper said, without citing sources. A Toyota spokeswoman said she is checking the validity of the report.

 New Delhi, July 7: Petroleum minister Mani Shankar Aiyar today said the government will set up a two-member committee, which will recommend ways to attract foreign investment in the country?s hydrocarbon sector.

 New Delhi, July 7: The board of trade headed by Kumar Mangalam Birla has roped in Apollo?s Omkar S. Kanwar and Essar?s Prashant Ruia to help promote exports. Five working groups and three special study groups have been set up to raise India?s share in world trade.

 New Delhi, July 7: The special purpose vehicle floated by Gail (India) Ltd and the National Thermal Power Corp to revive the 2,184-mw Dabhol power plant has been named Ratnagiri Gas and Power Pvt Ltd.

 New Delhi, July 7: Finance minister P. Chidambaram today cleared 28 foreign direct investment proposals worth Rs 204.82 crore, including those of HSBC, Standard Chartered Bank, General Motors and Ford Credit International.




